RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HERE KITTY KITTY stalked the pace to the turn, swept up three wide at the quarter pole to take command at the head of the lane and draw away as much best. JANE'S A DIVA broke alertly to lead from the gate, set a pressured pace to the top of the stretch and finished gamely to hold second. DABNEY bumped at the start, moved up from two wide early to press the pace, moved clear of the inside rival into the turn to duel on the lead from the rail to upper stretch and kept on to the wire only to miss the place. ABRA ABRA reserved off the early pace, rallied midway on the turn while circling wide and finished with a late bid. GOODY FOUR SHOES broke inward bumping and crowding rivals, dropped to the rear of the field to trail to upper stretch and showed some late interest along the rail down the lane. ANTE ANGEL rushed up the inside to be prominent nearing the turn, took back entering the turn and finished as no threat. SANTIVA DIVA squeezed between rivals leaving the gate, flashed speed from between rivals through the turn and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Ante Angel
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed up inside, taken back, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Dabney
ENTRY.OWNER: Nicks William A Spiess Stable LLC and Klopp Randy L
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, dueled inside, kept on

ENTRY.NAME: Goody Four Shoes
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bumped rival, inside late interest

ENTRY.NAME: Here Kitty Kitty
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, swept up 3w, took command, drew away

ENTRY.NAME: Jane's a Diva
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, set pressured pace, gamely, held second

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 75. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 17500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Ov er Since August 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMAZING GAL pressed the pace for the first half mile, assumed command into the far turn, opened a clear advantage and finished unchallenged. SECOND EXCHANGE tracked the leaders from the rail for the first half, dropped back losing position into the turn, circled four wide while being asked leaving the three-eighths pole and finished willingly to be gaining through the lane. ELUSIVE JUSTICE trailed early, ranged up three wide down the backside to chase the leader though the turn and flattened out in the lane. TIMELESS GLORY went one-paced as no threat throughout. NATIVE LION flashed speed for a half mile to duel on the lead from the rail and came up empty.

ENTRY.NAME: Second Exchange
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, lost position, circled 4w, finished well, 2d best

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: L.T.B. Inc, Ed Wright Cattle Company & Miles Childers

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 1M Turf CR: 82. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIQUID ADDICTION (IRE) saved ground in striking position along the fence while waiting patiently, rallied in the turn while tipping out to engage the pacesetter in upper stretch and finished in a determined drive. NEWS AT NINE sped to the lead up the rail into the first turn, opened a clear lead, settled to rate down the backside, widened again into the far turn and held well through the lane while unable to hold off the winner. HILTON HEAD tracked the leader from three wide through the final bend and failed to mount a closing rally. MOON WISH reserved well off the pace, circled at the head of the lane and finished with good energy to gain the minor placing. JOINT VENTURE settled off the pace down the backside, rallied up the rail to make a bid in mid-stretch and finished evenly. AUGUSTUS BLUE dropped back through the field to be near the rear down the backside, and rallied belatedly between rival in the stretch. NIGHT CHANT trailed for the first half mile and passed tiring rivals in the lane. CHANNEL Z stalked the pace from three wide through the far turn and weakened late in the drive. RED FIVE rated in mid-pack for three quarters and faded with out rally in the stretch. CREPE YARNS was never a threat. CENTAURO prompted the pace from two wide to the head of the lane and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 90. Allowance Purse 36000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, STATE BRED OR INDIANA BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs .; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 18 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M SO SORRY unhurried in the early going while taken in hand to settle at the back of the field, circled six wide in the far turn when called upon, took command in upper stretch and drew away handily down the lane. SAKE (FR) rated just off the leader down the backside, moved to the lead just leaving the quarter pole, opened a clear advantage briefly and was overhauled by the winner despite finishing willingly to be second best. MINT EDITION settled near the back of the field, mounted a rally from between horses on the far turn, worked through rivals to the inside and finished with good late energy. STAR WISHER stalked the pace from between rivals to be prominent turning for home and finished evenly. BEYOND DOUBT reserved well off the pace to the final bend and circled wide with a late gain. HARVEY'S PRINCESS made an early bid down the backside and flattened out in the turn. GIO'S BABY GIRL rated in mid-pack to the turn while between horses and failed to mount a rally. DICHOTOMY sped to the lead into the first turn, set a pressured pace for a half mile and gradually gave way. POND WALKER (GB) raced up three wide in the first turn to move to the leader, took the lead down the backside on a clear lead, was challenged into the final bend and tired coming home. APRIL'S GEM stalked the pace from four wide to the far turn and came up empty. RITAAN chased from three wide through the far turn and weakened turning for home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: middle move, took lead, outfinished, second best
